body: Hello. yes, you need either keep the second training set in a separate folder, re-name the outputs, etc. I would recommend making a new training set, (new date, etc in config file), and keeping it separate...

Were should I change the channel size? My configurations are as follows right now, but I get the same error:

It is not a variable. (because we assume one has RGB images...)

I don't know your data, but I suppose ```frame``` in this line 
https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/blob/master/deeplabcut/pose_estimation_tensorflow/predict_videos.py#L193

has ```ny x nx x ncolor``` dimensions, then you can assuming that the last channel is depth pass it on without the depth by:
```frame=frame[:,:,:2]```

But you need check that...
okay, it might also be a video type error, i.e. the default is .avi, and if your videos are something else, you need to set `videotype=mp4` for example)

I just was typing that I was using an mp4 video, I'll try changing the videotype. I'll let it know if it worked

Edit: Changing the videotype works!
